news.title: Birla Corporation's net profit increases by 127.59% in Q4 FY24
news.para: Birla Corporation's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,682.12 crore in Q4 FY24, a growth of 6.79 per cent from Rs 2,511.68 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Kansai Nerolac Paints' net profit up 18.76% in Q4 FY24
news.para: Kansai Nerolac Paints' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,801.92 crore in Q4 FY24, a growth of 3.36 per cent from Rs 1,743.29 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: HDFC Capital exits with Rs 298 crore return from Total Environment project in Bengaluru
news.para: HDFC Capital had invested Rs 229 crore in a residential apartment project located in Whitefield, Bangalore. The Investment was against development of 1mn sf of residential apartments in the project named “Pursuit of a Radical Rhapsody”.

news.title: Toronto home sales fall for third month in April
news.para: Seasonally adjusted sales declined 3.4% in April from the previous month after falling 2.4% in March, according to Toronto Regional Real Estate Board (TRREB) data.

news.title: Of seven lakh properties, just 1,363 harvest rainwater in Nagpur
news.para: As per data from NMC’s property tax department, 5,440 property owners or just 0.77% have implemented eco-friendly measures like RWH, solar energy use, wastewater recycling and reuse, and vermicomposting.

news.title: CBRE's revenue rise 7.1% to $7.94 billion in Q1 2024
news.para: "Leasing outperformed expectations, driven by office leasing growth globally," CBRE CEO Bob Sulentic said. The company's global leasing revenue rose 4%, led by a 9% growth in Asia-Pacific.

news.title: Shree Naman gets NCLT approval to take over Radius Infra
news.para: Radius Infra Holdings has a prime land parcel of nearly half an acre with development potential in Mumbai's Andheri area. The land parcel is set to be developed within 36 months under the NCLT approved resolution plan.

news.title: Godrej Properties to market realty projects developed by Godrej & Boyce for management fees
news.para: Godrej Properties Executive Chairperson Pirojsha Godrej said the company has been the development manager for the real estate projects and the same arrangement would continue.

news.title: Builders in Germany to strike in latest blow to troubled construction sector
news.para: Among other things, the deal proposed a raise of 250 euros per month from May 1, 2024, with a further increase on April 1, 2025, of 4.15% in western Germany and 4.95% in eastern Germany.

news.title: Raymond's net profit rises 18% to Rs 229 crore in Q4 FY24
news.para: Consolidated net revenue in the quarter under review was Rs 2,688 crore as against Rs 2,192 crore in the year-ago period, up 23 per cent, it added.

news.title: Aptus Value Housing Finance's net profit up 21.24% in Q4 FY24
news.para: Aptus Value Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 391.15 crore in Q4 FY24, a growth of 25.95 per cent from Rs 310.57 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: India Ratings maintains neutral outlook on construction sector for FY25
news.para: Ind-Ra expects EPC players to post a healthy performance in FY25, albeit with a moderation in the revenue growth rate, accompanied with a modest uptick in operating margins while maintaining adequate liquidity buffers.

news.title: CapitaLand India Trust acquires 2.5 million sq ft from Phoenix Group in Hyderabad
news.para: CapitaLand India Trust will provide funding of Rs 2.15 billion (S$34.68 million) to refinance the existing loan and receive interest on the funding at a rate which is higher than its borrowing cost.

news.title: Godrej Properties' net profit increases by 5.32% in Q4 FY24
news.para: Godrej Properties' net total consolidated income stood at Rs 1,914.82 crore in Q4 FY24, a growth of 4.13 per cent from Rs 1,838.82 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Shriram Properties acquires four acre land parcel in Bengaluru
news.para: Shriram Properties will develop a residential project encompassing around four lakh sq ft of aggregate saleable area. This project has revenue potential of over Rs 250 crore.

news.title: Mysuru civic body collects 46% property tax in April
news.para: According to MCC sources, officials of all nine zones have collected Rs 91.5 crore in property tax as against the target of Rs 199.9 crore for this fiscal year.

news.title: Brick by brick, Pirojsha changed the realty game at Godrej
news.para: Pirojsha Godrej's strategic leadership at Godrej Properties during the global financial crisis led to innovative approaches like joint developments and a capital-lite model. His focus on efficiency and immediate project launches propels the company's growth.

news.title: Banks homing in on a bigger share of expanding real estate pie
news.para: The real estate sector is growing across segments said property analysts. Top seven property markets in the country registered total sales of 74,486 apartments during the quarter.

news.title: SC order a relief, but Unitech buyers worried about funds
news.para: On April 26, a bench of Chief Justice DY Chandrachud and Justices JB Pardiwala and Manoj Misra modified its earlier order asking Noida Authority to approve revised layouts of Unitech on the entire land allotted to the builder without insisting on dues, which exceeds Rs 10,000 crore.

news.title: Max Estates to jointly develop 18.23 acres land in Gurugram
news.para: This land parcel is contiguous to its existing 11.80 acres of land on Dwarka Expressway in sector 36 A, Gurugram on which Max Estates had done a joint development agreement (JDA) last year.
